@startuml
!pragma svgparser sax
' Regression test: polygon points using space-separated coordinate format (SVG spec valid).
' The SVG spec (section 9.7.1) allows points as "x1,y1 x2,y2" OR "x1 y1 x2 y2" OR mixed.
' PlantUML must support both. Previously only comma-separated pairs were accepted; space-separated
' coordinates produced empty paths (no points parsed), causing Integer.MAX_VALUE bounding boxes
' when multiple such sprites appeared in the same diagram.

sprite arrow_space <svg viewBox="0 0 80 40" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <!-- Space-separated: "x y x y" format (also valid per SVG spec) -->
  <polygon points="0 20 60 0 60 15 80 15 80 25 60 25 60 40" fill="#ea4335"/>
</svg>

sprite chevron_space <svg viewBox="0 0 60 40" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <!-- Mixed format: some pairs comma-separated, others space-separated -->
  <polygon points="0,0 40,0 60,20 40,40 0,40 20,20" fill="#fbbc04"/>
</svg>

sprite star_space <svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <!-- Fully space-separated: x y x y ... -->
  <polygon points="50 10 61 35 88 35 67 57 76 81 50 65 24 81 33 57 12 35 39 35" fill="#4285f4"/>
</svg>

Alice -> Bob : Arrow <$arrow_space>
Bob -> Charlie : Chevron <$chevron_space>
Charlie -> Alice : Star <$star_space>

note right
  Space-separated polygon coords:
  <$arrow_space> arrow
  <$chevron_space> chevron
  <$star_space> star
end note
@enduml
